pull_request.title: Change dependabot to a monthly cadence
pull_request.body:
## Description of the change

Changing Dependabot's cadence for all ecosystems to monthly.

## Why am I making this change?

We don't need to update our dependencies more frequently unless there's a security concern.

## Checklist

- [x] I've updated the relevant CHANGELOG files if necessary. Changes to `javy-cli` and `javy-core` do not require updating CHANGELOG files.
- [x] I've updated the relevant crate versions if necessary. [Versioning policy for library crates](https://github.com/bytecodealliance/javy/blob/main/docs/contributing.md#versioning-for-library-crates)
- [x] I've updated documentation including crate documentation if necessary.

issue.title: GitHub Action for Dependabot PRs to run cargo vet
issue.body:
## What is the idea?

We should create a GitHub Action that runs for Dependabot PRs that will run `cargo vet` and update exemptions[^1].

## What problem does it solve?

At the present time, most Rust Dependabot PRs fail the `cargo vet --locked` check and can't be merged without manually making changes to the PR. Running `cargo vet` and updating exemptions should allow us to merge these PRs in a more timely manner.

[^1]: https://docs.github.com/en/code-security/dependabot/working-with-dependabot/automating-dependabot-with-github-actions
